 America, the continental islands of Trinidad and Tobago, and the Caribbean Netherlands off the Venezuelan coast. It includes identification keys and descriptions of all genera and species; comments on distribution; maps of localities; discussions of subspecies; and summaries of natural, taxonomic, and nomenclatural history. Rodents also contains a detailed list of cited literature and a separate gazetteer based on confirmed identifications from museum vouchers and the published literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMammalszSouth AmericavClassification. 0aMammalszSouth AmericaxGeographical distribution. 0aMammalszSouth America. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aD’Elía, Guillermo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPardiñas, Ulyses F. J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPatton, James L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226169606423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226169606.jpg  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles